<br>
Now if you had a flowing thought item that made you get back 10% more mana in the time it takes to get back the 90 mana you would get 99 mana, which is close enough to the original cost.  11.111... % is the precise number needed to get back to 100 mana in the time it would have taken you to get 90 mana back.  Since you only need 90 mana to cast the 100 mana spell it can be seen as a 11.111% FT item I guess. <br>
<br>
What's even more impressive is the fact that since spells cost 90% of what they originally did, not only are you 11.1111% more effective (over time), your mana pool is effectively expanded by 11.1% as well... (something FT items don't do).<br>
<br>
I think it's better to look at it this way... a percent increase in effectiveness.  It would be true that the faster you get mana back the more that 11.1% would mean in straight numbers, but it may be a bit misleading to look at it that way. <p><table>
